title: Gen AI Training Path: Technical Track
description: AI Learning paths set by Encora Inc

title: AI-Powered Software and System Design
description: Course by Deep Learning via Coursera. This course explores how AI can be integrated into software and system design processes to enhance efficiency and innovation.

title: Team Software Engineering with AI
description: Course by Deep Learning via Coursera. This course focuses on the application of AI in team-based software engineering projects, emphasizing collaboration and productivity.

title: Introduction to Generative AI for Software Development
description: Course by Deep Learning via Coursera. This is the introductory course in the Generative AI for Software Development specialization, covering the basics of generative AI and its applications in software development.

title: LangChain for LLM Application Development
description: Course by Deep Learning introduction to LangChain for LLM Application Development. LLM is used to build applications powered by language models. Not my fav language, Python, but good to understand the concepts.

title: Gen AI Training Path: Foundational
description: AI Learning paths set by Encora Inc. First learning path about Generative AI concepts and applications.

title: Advanced Prompt Engineering for Everyone
description: Course by Vanderbilt University via Coursera. This course covers advanced techniques in prompt engineering for AI models. I found better courses about this since this is not pointing at day by day developer tasks.

title: Generative AI: Prompt Engineering Basics
description: Course by IBM via Coursera. This course introduces the basics of prompt engineering for generative AI models, focusing on effective techniques to elicit desired outputs from AI systems. Nice tips and tricks.

title: Generative AI with Large Models
description: Course by Deep Learning AI via Coursera. This course covers the fundamentals of working with large language models (LLMs) and their applications in various domains. It uses mostly Python for the examples.

title: AWS: Compute and Storage
description: Course by Deep Learning AI via Coursera. This is one of the series of courses to prepare for the AWS Certified Developer - Associate exam. All the products of AWS oriented to compute and storage are covered in this course.

title: Generative AI for Everyone
description: Course by Deep Learning AI via Coursera. This is first course of the GenAI learning path by Encora. It covers the basics of generative AI. This course provides an overview of generative AI concepts.

title: AI Software Testing with Gemini
description: Course by Dan Andrei Bucureanu. I Personally use Gemini a lot to study. I wished it would be more updated since it runs older versions almost deprecated of Gemini. It also compares results with other LLMs.

title: ChatGPT Prompt Engineering for Developers
description: Course by AWS via Coursera. I really started my journey with Prompt Engineering with this course. It covers all the basics and some advanced concepts to get better results from LLMs. I wish it would cover more models than just GPT but it worked so well to start with.

title: Exam Prep: AWS Certified SysOps Administrator - Associate Specialization
description: Course by Whizlabs Instructors. This is the specialization to prepare for the AWS Certified SysOps Administrator - Associate exam. It covers all the topics needed to pass the exam and get the certification. This is a huge pool of knowledge that I treasure the most

title: AWS Cloud Technical Essentials
description: Course by Amazon Web Services. This course is the real big picture of everything that AWS offers. It covers all the main services and products of AWS, giving a good overview of the cloud computing platform.
